               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1559" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1559" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1559" type="surname" value="FAULKNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1559" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES FAULKNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a whitesmith, in the employ of George Giles Weston Thatcher, an ironmonger and brazier, at Clapham. On the morning of the 20th of Sept., about half-past eleven o'clock, the prisoner came to the workshop—he did not ask for anything—I saw him take the tap off the board, and put it into his pocket—I did not see him pick the brass crank up—he sat there a little while—I went in to see if my master was in the front shop, and while I was gone he walked out—this is my master's property.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you see me take it off the bench? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I can swear to this tap—I took it out of the boiler myself, and put a new one on—I saw you take it off the board on the window ledge, and put it into your pocket—you did not take it from one pocket and put it into another.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1560" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1560" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
