                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1561" type="given" value="GEORGE GILES WESTON"></interp>GEORGE GILES WESTON THATCHER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an ironmonger, at Clapham. I have seen this tap about the premises, on the bench—I cannot swear to it—there is always a good deal of metal lying about—the prisoner never worked for me—I have known him at work at different shops in Clapham for these two years.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> It is my own property.</p>
